# Bug: pop/pop2 of a side-effect-free, non-statement value rendered as a bare expression statement.
# Seed: org.springframework.cglib.core.EmitUtils (spring-core 5.3.27). javac left dead `aload x; pop`
# pairs in process_array/string_switch/etc.; the decompiler used to emit them as `var0;`, which javac
# rejects as "not a statement" (14 errors, the spring-core tree-recompile blocker). Per JLS 14.8 such
# discarded bare locals/constants/class refs are dropped (keepDiscardedStackValue). Kill-switch
# JDEC_POP_ELIDE_OFF restores the legacy bare-statement emission (see TestPopElideIsLoadBearing).
#
# No bare local-variable-only statement line may appear in the output.
-/(?m)^\s*var\d+;\s*$/
# The method that contained the dead pop still decompiles (the call that followed the dropped pop).
+if_icmp(155,
